##Fighting to the Middle: A medical aid team's Wuhan Memories | first line diary

MICRO-SIGNAL BQSHENYIDU

Beijing Youth Daily reports from the official public number

Reporter / Liu Mi

Editor / Song Jianhua

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Shijitan hospital nurse Liu Yuhang took off the mask for a moment

The No. 579 bus has not been to Jiangtan Park, one of Wuhan's landmarks, for more than a month, and has been used as a ferry for the Beijing medical team, shuttling between Sanjiahu road and Wuhan Xiehe West Courtyard. From mid-afternoon to early morning, the only passengers on the Empty Street were doctors and nurses.

On January 27, a medical team from 12 hospitals in Beijing arrived in Wuhan to take over the three wards of Xiehe West Hospital. As of 9:00 on March 5,302 patients had been admitted and 70 people had been discharged, the vast majority of whom were severe and critically ill.

Before I left with the medical team, I could imagine that most of this time, would be composed of patients, family members, and medical staff. But when it came to concrete characters and stories, the impact was greater than I could have imagined.

At one end of the scale is a 50-minute ride on a shared bicycle to find a bed, write a commitment and a family member who does not want to take up too much of the medical resources; At the other end of the spectrum are SARS veterans returning to isolation, their memories awakened, and Post 95 nurses who have just begun to intubate patients at high risk.

The scales are balanced not only by skill, but also by will and heart.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Medical team members in protective gear

January 27: A war

This is the first time I've ever heard anyone compare it to a war.

On the way to the airport, Tang Ziren, leader of Chaoyang Hospital, said a line from a war movie to the team members: "inside of us, I will set foot on Wuhan First, and leave at last, I will bring you back safely. "

A few days before departure, Ruan Zheng, a nurse at Xuanwu Hospital, was a little angry. Her husband, a policeman, was calm about everything. He seemed to have no special reaction to her coming to Wuhan. Until about the time of departure, colleagues pulled her husband to her, Ruan Zheng found him crying like a child.

Ruan Zheng for a moment, took out a mobile phone and said: "Come, record, 20 years, the first time to see you shed tears. "

At 8:30 p.m. , as the flight was about to take off, the captain spoke with a lump in his throat, comparing the medical team members to "heroes, " and taking pride in the fact that he was about to fly to Wuhan.

January 28th: "It's contaminated. "

The medical team set off from their residence on Sanjiahu road. Ten minutes later, the 579 bus, which was used as a ferry, stopped at the gate of Xiehe West Hospital in Wuhan. The first docking of the medical team was about to begin.

After getting out of the car, everyone froze for a few seconds and saw in the distance the patients in the fever clinic hovering around with CT scans.

Suddenly someone shoved a bag into my pocket and pulled it out to see a more protective N95 mask. "Put this on too, you that can't" , to my mask is the male nurse Wang Changliang Xuanwu Hospital, we just met in the car. After whispering in my ear, he walked away.

The medical team was taken to the side entrance of the Union and Western hospital, where the inpatient building was to be used as soon as they entered. Local medical staff in Wuhan repeatedly warned not to pass by the fever clinic just now, "there has been contaminated. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wang Changliang and Tang Ziren / Gao Zhao

February 1st: Awakened Memories

The first time out of the isolation ward in Wuhan, someone asked Tang Ziren and SARS when compared to what is the feeling, in 2003, he is Chaoyang Hospital into the fever clinic one of the first doctors. Tang asked with a smile, "I was 33 then, and now I'm 50. What do you think? "

The moment he put on the suit, Xuanwu Hospital Doctor Li Yan's memory of 17 years ago was awakened, choking, claustrophobic, and wrapped in stress. As a smoking doctor, she knew that people could even tolerate a knife, acupuncture, but the most intolerable is suffocation.

Deja Vu. The patients in the ward. Seventeen years ago, a man in his 70s, surnamed Yang, entered Li Yan's SARS ward and died a week later. The same day, the same bed and live in a 30-year-old woman, also surnamed Yang. Li Yan later learned that they were father and daughter.

Among the team's first patients in Wuhan was an elderly couple in their 60s who insisted on staying in the same room so they could look out for each other. But two people are suspected cases, must be isolated, Wang Changliang advised for a long time, they accepted to live in the arrangement of the door.

February 2: Bad News

Li Yan told me that the old couple, who wanted to share a room, had died.

The old man's son could not return from the provinces, and the formalities had to be signed by her husband. "Bad news" is never easy to deliver in isolation rooms, with heavy protective gear, eyes and body language providing little comfort.

Li Yan and his colleagues had a plan in place. If the old man wouldn't sign, if he got emotional, or even if he hurt himself, they had a crash cart parked out front.

Entering the ward, Li Yan told the old man, his wife's condition is indeed very serious, early treatment done, "my aunt died in vain, but please rest assured, my aunt died peacefully, without any pain. "

The old man cried bitterly, and Li Yan watched with a twinge of guilt. "At the end of the day, we couldn't even get them in the same room. "

Li Yan told another lie, and the old man asked her if her wife had left any words. In fact, the old lady left very suddenly, soon fell into a coma, but Li Yan or crossbow said: "Aunt said, let you live, so you can replace him to continue to live. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan residents armed to the teeth for shopping

February 3rd: "like a deserter. "

My cousin introduced me to her classmate Cheng Xiao in Wuhan, they read together medical, two years ago Cheng Xiao from a three-a hospital in Wuhan, the Department of infection resigned.

Cheng Xiao said he has never had too much yearning for the doctor profession, after work also do not like to do experiments, published papers. Outbreak, many people around him said he "escaped" , but Cheng Xiao is not comfortable, a kind of "desertion" feeling.

It had nothing to do with professional pride, he explained, except that colleagues in the department had been kind to him. "At this point, I should be with someone I care about. "

Every day, we received news from our former colleagues from the hospital. The number of registered doctors and nurses in the fever clinic had increased several times. which doctors and nurses were being quarantined? Cheng Xiao wanted to do something. He joined a volunteer group to audit the medical supplies he had collected, also asked the former section chief, as an ordinary person, can return to the isolation ward on duty.

Cheng Xiao also told me about his uncle, after the Spring Festival, the old man first caught a cold for a few days, then coughed to hold his breath, for fear of cross-infection, has not been to the hospital.

Cheng Xiao grew up in a good relationship with his uncle, who used to be a teacher, and retired to teach other people. He liked his uncle learned's casual way of doing things.

February 6: pull back one by one

At 9 a.m. , Li Yan heard about a patient who was getting sicker, with his oxygen mask on full blast and his Oxygenation in his late 70s and 80s.

Li Yan called the ICU, contacted the bed, and stressed that the patient was of salvage value. When she changed into her protective clothing and entered the ward, the nurse shouted, "Is there a doctor? Is there a doctor? "

After spattering the floor with coffee-colored blood, the patient went into a coma with a heart rate of 167, cyanotic from the extreme lack of oxygen.

Li Yan wanted to establish an immediate venous access in preparation for the subsequent infusion of salvage drugs. Patients have been eating very little, blood vessels are not easy to find, a few pool of hospital nurses first in the toe found a blood vessel, just injected a stimulant, the needle drum.

Several nurses were almost on top of the patient, trying to find another way quickly. No one knows if there will be another splash, which is one of the highest risk of infection. The goggles were so misty that Li Yan could barely see the patient, and she didn't know how the nurses had managed to find another vein in her wrist.

Unable to take a blood gas, Li Yan had to rely on clinical experience to speculate that the patient had acidosis from lack of oxygen, and that the Sodium bicarbonate had been injected. After a while, the patient regained consciousness, and the ICU came back with the news that a bed was available.

"without a link, this person might not survive, " Li Yan said. Such scenes happen almost every day in the ward, just like in the battlefield, dodging bullets and bringing back as many patients as they can.

Li Yan and Hongyun Chen Zhao Gao

February 7: Goodwill Estrangement

The Union hospital needed to increase the number of beds to 800 and expand the ward again, a problem that worried the hospital staff for several days.

In Infectious Disease Hospital, hospital sense prevention and Control Department has a "veto power" on many matters. But in the epidemic area, outside the system also have to consider the constraints of human and resources.

As of today, the Beijing Medical Team has opened three wards on the 8th, 10th and 12th floors, with a total of 155 patients admitted. Shifts of medical staff and the wearing of protective equipment are carried out in the clean area. In order to expand capacity, the hospital group finally came up with the idea of reducing the number of clean areas, three wards sharing a clean area.

Faced with the increased risk, the sense of hospital team required all members to treat their peers as potential "suspected cases" , and some well-meaning "distancing" occurred around me.

After the interview nurse Chen Hongyun, the photographer to take photos for her, I offered to help Chen Hongyun take a coat, she refused, "don't touch, I have entered the ward, not good for you. "

Upstairs, Chen Hongyun and put forward to wait for another lift, said the same sentence: "I have entered the ward. "

We do not want to make so unripe cent, determined to let Chen Hongyun also into the elevator. Inside, she kept her distance until we got out of the elevator and she pressed her floor.

8 February: Fever Clinic

Cheng Xiao suddenly told me that he and his cousin accompanied his uncle to a hospital fever clinic. My uncle's condition worsened suddenly in the early morning. He was not only showing symptoms of pneumonia, but also was not in his right mind. His mouth was all crooked.

The night before, Cheng Xiaogang and I had talked about the dangers of entering the fever clinic, but there were still a lot of accompanying family members, and our final conclusion was that there were people we cared about.

I asked Cheng Xiao how the protective measures, he said a sister to the medical N95 mask, but because of urgent travel, he forgot to take the goggles.

Cheng Xiao told me the news in the fever clinic, a taxi down two old people, a mother-in-law holding a GRANDPA almost collapsed on the ground, shouted a few no one came to help. Cheng Xiao is about to go up, a bed with the male family took a step ahead, while reprimanding people's indifference, while GRANDPA back in.

Cheng Xiao also met two college classmates, wearing protective clothing, he recognized the eyes of two people. One is a hematologist, now uncle Cheng Xiao's tube bed doctor, and the other is an ophthalmologist, who now counts nucleic acid test results.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Pedestrians wearing protective clothing on a street in Wuhan

February 9: The two ends of the scale

In the afternoon, several wards of the medical team were informed that Concorde West Hospital would transfer some of the patients who had improved to other hospitals to make room for new beds.

Oxygenation, basic medical history and age, are considered criteria, according to the medical records, Liyan reported several bed number. This is not an easy process, if in normal times, doctors do not let patients who are just getting better go through the twists and turns of transfer.

But it's a "wartime" situation, Li Yan told me of a concept called "triage, " in which soldiers are marked with different colored strips on the battlefield, and doctors are quick to make decisions based on the patient's condition.

As I watched the doctors finalize the list of patients to be transferred, Cheng Xiao sent me a message that his uncle was waiting for a spare bed at Concorde West Hospital.

My uncle had been diagnosed with new coronary pneumonia and was in a coma. The doctor suggested we find a bed in the ICU. Cheng Xiaoxian uncle transferred to the fever clinic of the observation ward, because everyone around said, live here can be priority transfer to the Western hospital.

Cheng Xiao to go to school with his professor to call, there is also very difficult, said a few days ago to help others find a bed just rejected.

On this day, I seem to see both sides of the scale.

10 February: Ward attendants

Cheng Xiao told me that last night, uncle finally live in the concord West Hospital, he and cousin also went to accompany. When they get out, they're going to quarantine themselves.

He explained that his uncle was in the general ward of the other medical teams and did not have as many nurses as the ICU. "But he was in a coma, and he couldn't live without people. "

"Do you have a suit? "

Cheng didn't know whether to comfort me or himself, saying they had masks and plenty of gloves. "We don't know how long we're going to be in there, " he said. "It's hard to keep wearing protective clothing. It doesn't mean much. "

My cousin also know about Cheng Xiaojin Ward, she sent me a photo, is a few of their classmates New Year in Wuhan to meet the group photo. They went to a concert in the sports centre next to the Western wing of Concorde, which has now been converted into a shelter hospital.

The medical staff are ready to take the patient's box lunch to the ward

February 11: The mental curve

Tang Ziren every day in the medical team contact group to forward a song, he believes in the power of music. Retweeting the 2003 Song Hand in hand, he said he always listened to it when he was on duty for SARS.

These are lessons from the SARS period.

In 2003 in the SARS ward days, Tang Ziren experienced the initial tension, two weeks after the gradual recovery, to more than a month later, fatigue, loneliness, anxiety again. In some cases, he spoke in the morning and the bed was empty in the afternoon. He turned on the television to relax. News of the outbreak was everywhere. He had also heard that, for his own reasons, no one dared to take an elevator with his mother.

Something similar is happening now. After 95 nurse Zhang Jun always remembers the old man that nursed before, the old person presses the bell to call the number to be particularly many times, is to change the urine bag this kind of nursing need mostly.

Zhang Jun was pleased with the visits. When a patient needed something to talk to, he was in good spirits. The last time they spoke, the old man asked Zhang Jun to take some of the fruit to a chair closer to him.

Zhang Jun next day to go on duty, the bed changed, the old man has gone, the new patient is in need of rescue.

Zhang Jun, who works in the Tuberculosis Department of the Beijing Chest Hospital, has seen patients leave, but the course of the disease will be slow, mostly can have a psychological preparation.

February 12: Death cases discussed

Each group of shift, have to inform the changes in the ward, XX aggravated, XX left, some bed was reported out, the next doctor will show surprised expression.

A doctor on the medical team with decades of clinical experience told me that, in his experience, looking at a patient's lab results, imaging studies, and past medical history, he had a good chance of estimating where the patient's body would be in the next few days. But in the volatile course of NCP, some of his patients, who had hoped for it, became worse than expected, "especially those who died in their 60s and 70s, which is not a very old age. "

There was only so much to go on from the existing cases, and at a seminar in the 12th floor Ward, five recently deceased patients were the subject of discussion.

The five patients, all elderly, were in a serious condition when they were admitted. Before they died, they experienced a sudden drop in Oxygenation. One of the patients had gone to the bathroom before he died, a local doctor at Concorde Hospital recalled, "and found that he was unconscious inside. "

Shijitan hospital leader Ding Xinmin that this is a very key clue, in the subsequent comb found that five patients have three people died before going to the bathroom.

Ding Xinmin analysis, new pneumonia patients on oxygen support demand is great, to the toilet need to take off the oxygen mask, but also cost physical strength. Even if some patients resist, when necessary, or insist on the use of Urinary Catheter.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The doctor discusses the CT images of the patient

13 February: send a comrade

In the afternoon, four confirmed patients were discharged from the Beijing Medical Team Ward. One of them was a nurse from a hospital in Wuhan. Tang Ziren was coming to see them off.

In addition to an apple symbolizing peace, Tang also handed over an envelope with the words "fight to the death, through thick and thin, to meet the Rainbow" and the money collected by several medical team members.

The nurse wants to evade, was again blocked by Tang Ziren to go back, "you are very not easy, I have respect to you. "

Seventeen years ago, Tang Ziren was involved in receiving the first SARS patient in Chaoyang Hospital, with a strong "virulence" . Two or three days later, he began to have colleagues fever, and then more than 20 medical staff infected. Looking at the side of the comrades-in-arms down, Tang Ziren said that the fear can not be described in words.

"It's like in a war movie, when you charge, it's a state of stress, hormones are running high, you get shot, you probably don't even feel it. When you calm down, you realize you have a big hole in your body and shrapnel is in it. "

Later in the day, Tang Ziren also dreamed of the day in isolation ward, but are not a nightmare. Only once did he walk past a monument in Beijing to the nine medical staff who died during the SARS epidemic and spend a long time there alone.

February 13: intubation

In the offices of the cleaning area, a dozen doctors and nurses are in a heated discussion, each raising his or her voice in order to be heard. In order to improve the rescue effect for the critically ill patients, the three wards of Beijing medical team will begin to intubate and use the invasive suction machine.

The decision led to a series of changes: a Ward was set aside as a specialized emergency room; shifts of nurses needed to be adjusted, with two people devoted to intubating patients; and the issue of financing suction machines and accessories, general three a hospital has only a few dozen of the breathing machine.

Before coming to Wuhan, Li Yan divided the team into "ordinary" and "monitoring" groups, but she did not expect that eventually the general ward would be converted into an intensive care unit for intubated patients. This is related to the existing ICU resources at intensive-care unit, which has only about 20 beds, which critically ill patients can enter, once had to be repeatedly weighed.

Li Yan's biggest concern was the safety issue, the patient's airway being opened up and connected to his lungs, where a splash could occur at any time. In principle, the infectious disease surveillance must be negative pressure ward, the fresh air system will continue to have the virus out of the air, but the existing conditions, can do only open windows ventilation.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The medical staff took the bag containing the body into the ward

February 14: the Yellow Bag

Yesterday near midnight, Cheng Xiao told me, uncle left.

After entering the isolation ward, Cheng Xiao has not wanted to use the doctor's thinking to consider uncle's illness, afraid of crying out to affect the care, also affect cousin's mood.

Yesterday morning, the uncle had symptoms of gastrointestinal bleeding, and in the evening appeared "head breathing" , which is the terminal symptoms of many patients, each inhalation head will be thrown back. Cheng Xiao Remembered, uncle the next day as a difficult case, please the area experts to discuss, he knew it takes a lot of energy to prepare, went to the doctor, "people may not, you are afraid to change the case. "

Uncle's high pressure fell to only 70 or 80, the doctor asked whether to intubate, Cheng Xiao and cousin hesitated, uncle had said before, do not like lying in bed like that.

When Cheng Xiao returned to the ward, uncle no movement, heart rate is only 17. He was in there for a while, came out, said it was time for an ekg. Only a former doctor would know that this is how hospitals keep records of people whose hearts have stopped beating.

Near midnight, Cheng Xiao and cousin to help the nurse, put uncle into the written "sacrifice" word yellow bag. When the undertaker arrived, he asked for another layer of bags to be put on the outside before the body was taken away.

Cheng Xiao and cousin contact the community, put forward as close contact personnel isolation, but the community said that can not find the car, two people back to the ward for a night.

The next day, I gave Cheng Xiao Protective clothing finally came in Handy, a student on duty in the West Hospital actively pulled him and his cousin to the quarantine point, the car, three people have put on protective clothing.

February 15: the feeling of war

After starting to care for the intubated patient, Wang Changliang and Ruan Zheng both wore protective face screens. Over the next few hours, they regularly turn over the intubated patient, suction the sputum, and change the urine bag. When they walked out again, for the first time in two weeks, they made a victory sign for my camera.

To ensure the patient's nutrition and medical supplies, the ward began a deep vein puncture, a routine procedure in the emergency room for Tang, but after wearing four layers of gloves, he tried several times to sterilize it with alcohol cotton. All he could rely on was muscle memory, pushing the needle into the collarbone, then pulling it back, raising the end of the needle again, pressing it against the lower edge of the collarbone and letting the dark red blood flow out

Most of the nurses in the Beijing medical team have devoted themselves to the care of the intubated patients. The nursing work in other wards requires additional manpower in the Union Medical College. A group of nurses from the West Wing headquarters had been transferred, and they all looked very young.

After the matron had familiarized them with the procedure of taking off their protective clothing, he told the man on duty to take the new nurses to the isolation ward and "go in for an hour and see. "

This is the first time I feel like this is a war. In the heat of the battle, the young recruits are the only ones who come in.

I told Li Yan, who agreed with the matron. She uses the analogy of the upcoming film nineteen seventeen, in which two young soldiers are sent through enemy trenches to deliver an important message during World War I.

"They may not have had much experience and ideals at first, but after seeing their comrades fall and seeing the cruelty, they have completed their transformation. "

A discharged patient holds an apple and a blessing from a medical team

February 19:50 minutes by bike

The hospital discharged 31 patients at one time. Wu Hansheng was the most excited one. Doctors and nurses in the ward were covered by protective clothing, Wu Hansheng remembered their voices, said a few words in the crowd, he called out everyone's name.

"I felt like a homeless person before I came here, " he wrote, clutching a few pages of thank-you notes. "When I came to the Western courtyard, my home was here! "

In fact, Wu Hansheng's home is in Hanyang District, but he hasn't been back for more than half a month. He developed a fever on January 25, and the community gave him a hotel key and told him to go there.

The hotel parking lot charges 50 yuan a day for parking. Wu Hansheng is a little angry. After the nucleic acid test, he parks his car and goes home. A few days later, Wu Hansheng got positive test results.

In early February, in his hotel room, Wu Hansheng had a fever of more than 38 degrees. He took a pill to reduce his fever by half. He did not dare to brush his teeth. He did not have the strength to walk from the bed to the bathroom, and his sputum still had blood in it. He called various departments to ask when he could go to the hospital, and the answer was to wait, wait, wait.

Wu sent a video to his wife, telling her where to put the valuables in the property certificate, and told her that if he left, his ashes would either be scattered in the ink lake in Hanyang District or near his mother's grave, which had died the year before last.

At 6 a.m. on Feb. 5, with no referral scheduled, Wu Hansheng didn't want to wait any longer. Instead, he said, he rode a 53-minute bike-share to try his luck at the Union Western hospital. He sent me a screenshot of the APP, too, in case I didn't believe him.

That day Wu Hansheng really checked into the ward, he later learned, just happened to have an old man died, free a bed.

21 February: A can of protein powder

I know Wang Liqiang because I saw the letter of commitment he wrote when his parents moved into the 8th floor ward.

"If there is an emergency while the parents are in the hospital, we do not want to take drastic measures... We believe that parents in the final moments of life do not want to occupy too much of the public health resources, worthy of their ordinary and great life."

When I called Wang for the first time a few days ago, his voice was tired. He said he didn't want to talk more. "My father has gone. "

Wang's parents, who had been in a nursing home for years because they were not in their right mind and needed primary care, speculated that the infection might have also occurred there. "If my father had been in his right mind, he would never have let us cause too much trouble to society, " he said

My father, a former bureau official in the education system, was strict with his children. "Forget about school. We never even took his bus. "

The second time we spoke, Wang Liqiang wanted to ask me something. His sister was also in the 8th floor ward. He wanted me to take a message to the doctor and take care of her.

Wang Liqiang has been living in Beijing all these years. When his parents were not admitted to the hospital, he was afraid that his aunt would get infected. His sister closely cared for the old man for four days and four days, sleeping only six hours. He felt very sorry for his sister.

I told him not to worry about the doctors'professional attitude and sense of responsibility, which was not a simple relief. Dr. Chohan, from the eighth floor ward, is also a Wuhan native who lives in Beijing.

Chohan went to Beijing after graduation. He not only had a family in Wuhan, but also studied medicine in Wuhan. Some of his classmates got to the front line before him. For these medical students, Wuhan is a city that needs to be defended like "Zuting" , to join the medical team, Chohan did not need more reasons, "do not come, the heart can not get over that hurdle. "

My mother and many of my relatives were in Wuhan, and Chohan never saw them. The family wanted to visit him at the compound, even from a distance, thinking they were close, but Chohan refused.

I didn't tell him, but even before I met him, Chohan had told me about his parents in the hospital room, the couples who were in the hospital together, the mother and daughter, all of which made Chohan feel uneasy.

Today, Wang Liqiang called again, and my promise to him was fulfilled. A doctor brought a can of protein powder to his sister during rounds, Wang said. It's not very valuable, but it's warm to be in an isolation ward.

The two discharged patients waved to the medical staff

February 19: MODEL patient

One of the first young men admitted to the hospital was regarded as a "model patient" .

The young man is a doctor, began to fever, he sent his wife and children to another place, and from the Internet ordered a lot of supplies, told the courier to go far, only to go out to pick up.

In the hospital, the young man obviously did a lot of preparation, he can read some CT images, will be on treatment, medication to ask a lot of targeted questions, but also very much in accordance with the doctor's decision.

From the doctor's point of view, I hope every patient can keep a cool head and communicate smoothly. But in the matter of life and death, everyone's character, knowledge, circumstances, performance is not the same.

Shitan hospital leader Ding Xinmin has been advised that hospitalized patients use less mobile phones, and family contact once a day morning and evening enough. Not many people can do this, modern communication has become a "double-edged sword" at this time, to accept the vast amount of information, negative emotions can not be avoided, become more fearful.

The various treatments were no longer secret. A family member called and said four letters in a row, asking if there was such a device. The doctor took a long time to realize that he was talking about ECMO. A family member said he had access to the convalescent plasma, he wanted to use it on a relative; another patient, still recovering, rushed out of the hospital, saying his daughter had been intubated at another hospital and he wanted to donate blood.

21 February: The eve of the counteroffensive

Tang was more concerned about the changes in the wards than the figures in the news. The death rate in the three wards of the medical team was falling, and more of the critically ill patients were getting better.

Now rounds, Tang Ziren to say a lot of words, a patient may have to ask him more than 10 minutes of questions, Tang Ziren quite happy, "people have the strength, just have the heart to consider their own things. "

The nurses also noticed a change, with many patients' tastes "getting higher and higher" and their appetites returning and they could taste salt and water. A 91-year-old man, the hospital lunch box smell too weak, nurse from the residence to bring some strong taste to eat.

It was a bit like "the eve of the counteroffensive, " Li Yan had decided. One day she would write "General Attack, Operation Decapitation" in her work notes, but it would take some time to write those words down.

Just past that small night shift, the ward is a busy. After Li Yan performed a deep vein puncture on a intubated patient and then a coma patient with kidney failure, Li Yan decided it was acidosis, but was unable to do a blood filter for the time being and had to find a potassium lowering drug to replace it.

After a while, the nurse suddenly said, bed 51 is Oxygenation, a very sick old man who always takes off his oxygen mask. He looked over and saw that the mask was hanging on his chin. I had no choice but to fasten the old man to the bed with the restraint belt.

At 12:00 p.m. , bed 51 had another accident. The old man untied the restraint belt, oneself got down to the ground, the blood oxygen dropped to more than 50, the whole body turns purple. Li Yan and his men got the old man back into bed, and when they couldn't find a machine to intubate him, a doctor kept squeezing the oxygen bag under his mask. After 20 minutes, he finally got his blood oxygen back above 90.

February 24: empathy

A psychologist from Beijing said that medical staff in the affected areas should pay attention to the issue of "empathy. " In their contact with patients, they should think from the patients' point of view. Emotional reactions are the same as those of patients, "But you have to be able to get in and get out, or it will have a big impact on you. "

It's not an easy thing to do.

I became acquainted with Wang Changliang because of the matter of the mask. He told me earlier that in the isolation ward, he cared for his patients, but he didn't want to get too close, emotionally, for fear of getting sucked in.

Today, Wang Changliang suddenly told me that he went to see the old man whose wife had died in the first group of patients. The old man is recovering and has been transferred to another ward, but he is still in a bad mood. Wang Changliang said in the past, "you have to refuel Ah, " the old man did not speak, nodded to him.

I asked Wang Changliang, is not to maintain emotional distance, he said a happy expletive: "How to install X, also can not change the good heart. "

February 25: Re examined kinship

Been away from home almost a month.

The husband told Ruan Zheng that he cried when he saw her off because he was really scared. To Wuhan, Ruan Zheng has not taken off the protective clothing after the ligature photos sent to her husband, afraid he was worried. Ruan finally understood why her husband, a policeman, never told her about his work. The silence was not alienation, but another kind of love.

Li Yan never talked to her husband about what was going on in the isolation ward, and when they did, they communicated more with their children. Li Yan had been feeling guilty for nearly two decades, and Li Yan had gone to extremes to keep everyone in the room alive. Her husband said she was selfish and forgot that she was still a wife and a mother. She only went to one parent-teacher conference, and every time she worked overtime, she lied to her children that "there was an old man in the ward who had a nosebleed. ".

Wang Changliang has been worried about his son, always want to accompany him. The son was not at home all the time, and was already somewhat unhappy. He told Wang Changliang, "you ugly monster, don't want to see you. " In recent days, the son only had a smile on his face. He had "needs" for his father, and wanted his father to hurry back, show him the ocean.

Zhang Jun felt that her father had changed, and that she wanted to talk to him more every day. But the father still didn't know how to communicate with his daughter, always reporting what he did every day, where he went, desperately trying to find something to talk about. Zhang Jun thought it was adorable.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A group of newly arrived medical personnel are being trained

26 February: Final Positions

One doctor reckons that, as with SARS, the last remaining patients will be rounded up in a few hospitals as the disease is brought under control.

In the three wards of the medical team, the majority of patients are still in critical and critical condition. In addition to new pneumonia, some people also have kidney failure, Hemiplegia, dementia, and even thoracolumbar fractures. Here, it may be one of the last positions to stop the fire in the epidemic area.

Most were also prepared to stay longer, and on February 2nd the medical team called in a barber to give them a haircut, which was extended by another two days because of the large number of people who had signed up.

On Triangle Lake Road, the medical team's residence was one of the few places where people were always coming in and out, which attracted a few stray cats and dogs. Worried about hygiene, the medical team secretary half-jokingly said that getting too close to cats and dogs was punishable by push-ups. But every day after dinner, some team member put some leftovers in the doorway and looked at them from a distance.

February 27: Two lives

In the hotel isolation of Cheng Xiao and cousin finished two nucleic acid test, are negative.

What they were worried about now was their aunt at home, who was in a very bad mood. My aunt wouldn't answer the phone except for them, and on the other end of the line would always say, he just left us? ... When do we get the ashes back...

Cheng Xiao remembered his uncle before the coma, with his last words, let him to buy a cane. Cheng Xiao Guess, uncle is either really in to go home to prepare, or want to leave a hope for oneself.

Talking to me again, Wu Hansheng was as excited as when he first got out of the hospital. He was quarantined in his other house. Before going, he met his wife 10 meters away. She put all kinds of daily necessities on the car wearing protective clothing. His son was upstairs in the back. Wu Hansheng insisted on not letting him down.

Wu told me about his life, starting as a civil servant, quitting in the late 1990s to make some money in the steel business and buy several apartments. Then business went bad and he got older, and he went to work for a property company.

To prove to me what he had said, one afternoon, Wu Hansheng sent me a dozen videos and photos of him with his son, the bloody sputum he coughed up in the hotel quarantine, and the night scene on Jianghan road last Christmas, "peace and happiness in 2020, " he shouted to the throng

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On February 2nd, a female medical team member was having her hair cut

February 29: People who don't want to be heroes

For the past month or so, Tang and Li Yan have been the most I've ever heard of comparing the present to a war.

Tang Ziren likes watching war movies and knows historical heroes, but he doesn't want to be seen as a hero. He says he came to Wuhan to save lives. He believes more in the Jewish proverb on the wall of a medical research institute, "To save one person is to save the world. "

Li Yan didn't want to be a hero, either. She had the simplest of ordinary people's thoughts: "End this war and go home. "

One day in the early summer of 2003, at a resort in Huairou District, Beijing, Li Yan and his colleagues ended a two week quarantine. Across from the quarantine site was the Beijing Brewery, which brought them a lot of beer. There were taxis that came and volunteered to take them home.

It was a hot day, Li Yan remembered, and she could see her mother, shaking her fan, waiting for her at the door.
